Dear Colleague,

Thank you for submitting your SAS grant application. Your chair has been automatically notified to provide an assessment about your application. We will inform you of the decision when the application review process is completed.

Thank you.

Marie Carriere
Associate Dean (Research)

description.text: This metadata set defines the email template to be sent to the applicant when application's submitted.

content.text: Applicant Information

The Adjudication committee is a multi-disciplinary committee. Please write for someone who does not understand your work and/or field.
Be clear and concise in your explanations, and make sure your justifications are detailed.

description.text: Please use your UAlberta CCID email address.

content.text:
Chair’s Contact Information

When the applicant is a Department Chair, the Dean's information must be provided.
Project Details

description.text: Describe your research project and explain why this is a necessary and urgent application for funding. Maximum 250 words.

name.text: Does this project involve human or animal subjects?

content.text: Please note that proof of ethics approval may be required before any grant awarded will be released. For more information concerning ethics clearance, please refer to the Research Ethics Office website.

name.text: Has Ethics approval already been obtained for this project?

content.text:
Budget Details

Conference Travel

All travel expenses are reimbursed in compliance with the UAPPOL Travel Expense Policies

  • For conference travel, EFF SAS allows one night before and one night after a conference to a maximum of 7 days.
  • Applicants must include detailed estimates of their transportation and hotel costs.These should be from travel agents, hotels, and / or travel booking websites.Combined travel and hotel estimates are not accepted.
  • Limits:
    • Conference travel in Canada / US maximum - $2, 250.00
    • Conference travel to all other destinations maximum - $3, 350.00

Please specify the travel cost breakdown and attach supporting documentation below.Please enter numerical values only.Do not use $ or, when entering your dollar values.
Dates of Conference

description.text: Includes: Airfare, trip cancellation insurance, seat selection and baggage fees
See UAPPOL Travel Expense Procedure, Appendix A: Schedule of Allowable Travel Expenses for allowable amounts and breakdown.
Transportation to/from airport/home only
Includes bus, train, car rental, travel insurance, visas, incidentals NOT already included in Airfare, Accommodation or Ground Transportation

Please attach the required travel and conference supporting documentation here as a single PDF document. [Be sure to review the section of the Policies and Procedures on required supporting documentation]
Explain the significance of this conference to your research and scholarly career. Maximum 250 words.

content.text:
Research and Creative Activity

Travel

  • Research travel has no time limit, but will be funded to a maximum of $5,000.00
  • Applicants must include detailed estimates of their transportation and hotel costs. These should be from travel agents, hotels, and/or travel booking websites. Combined travel and hotel estimates are not accepted.

Please specify the travel cost breakdown and attach supporting documentation below. Please enter numerical values only. Do not use $ or , when entering your dollar values.

description.text: Includes: Airfare, trip cancellation insurance, seat selection and baggage fees
See UAPPOL Travel Expense Procedure, Appendix A: Schedule of Allowable Travel Expenses for allowable amounts and breakdown.
Transportation to/from airport/home only
Includes bus, train, car rental, travel insurance, visas, incidentals NOT already included in Airfare, Accommodation or Ground Transportation

Please attach the required travel and conference supporting documentation here as a single PDF document. [Be sure to review the section of the Policies and Procedures on required supporting documentation]
Explain how this travel is essential to advancing your research. Maximum 250 words.

content.text: Personnel and Services
Failure to provide a detailed estimate will result in automatic disqualification of this part of the application.

name.text: Description of personnel to be hired or services to be purchased

description.text: <i>Provide and outline of the type of work to be undertaken, the expected time frame for completing that work, and a comment on why it is essential to your research. Maximum 250 words.</ i>

content.text: Estimate for Hiring Students

For each student to be hired, click 'Add' and indicate whether the student will be an undergraduate, MA, or PhD student, and specify the period for which they will be hired, the number of hours to be worked, and related calculations. Applicants are expected to adhere to the Collective Agreement when calculating salaries for graduate students. Research budgets for casual student labour must reflect the minimum rate (award + salary + benefits) for Doctoral and Masters students.

name.text: Provide details and calculations as specified above

description.text: Personnel Budget Item

content.text: Estimates for Contracted Services

For each contracted service, click 'Add' and then provide the requested information. Please describe the services to be provided. Note that you must also attach written estimates for all contracted services. Estimates should be combined into one single PDF document.

name.text: Provide details and calculations as specified above

description.text: Personnel Budget Item

Attach written estimate for contracted services as single PDF document.
[Required if funding requested for professional services]
Why are these services required for this project at this time? [Maximum 250 words]

description.text: Provide a description of the materials and equipment you plan to purchase and outline why they are essential to your research project at this time. Maximum 250 words.

description.text: Please list your scholarly and/or creative publications over the past 5 years. Include conference presentations, displays, and exhibits or performances. Complete CVs will not be accepted.

content.text:
Save or Submit Your Application

To save a partially completed application and work on it later, please click on the Save button below.
If you have completed your application want to submit it, please use the Submit button instead. In order to submit your appplication, you must fill all required fields. Submitted applications cannot be modified.
NOTE: If you successfully saved or submitted the application, your application form should disapear from this page and you whould see a success message. If this wouldn't happen, then your session may be timed out. If so, please KEEP THIS BROWSER TAB OPEN and sign in again with a DIFFERENT tab on the SAME BROWSER. Once you signed in, try to save or submit your application again.
